\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid9402713 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You grew up in this North Bay area did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No, I - I was brought up in - in - in the Glen,
 that's right, yes. And Mary - Mary is living there just now. Yes. Oh I was about the building if that house as a boy, yes. Had to take the jumpers to the smoothie and things like that and hear them chaffing and - breaking stones and - then I left, I came
 to Edinburgh. I was - spent five - about five and a half years in Edinburgh, then I went down to Birmingham. From there I came to Manchester. And from Manchester I came back to the place where I had started and stayed there until I left - for good.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 When you were a child did you have any little jobs you had to do regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh yes, there're plenty of jobs of course at that time - peet was the - was the main means of - of - of - fuel you see, and - we had to carry - carry these - a bag of these - or two bags of these peats - home every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 At what age did you have to start doing that, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh - well - say about ten or so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 It was heavy wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, but hard - you were hard in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did the girls also carry peat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Yes. Yes. They took their share. Yes. And of course the - there was the peat cutting. Before you started - the peat carrying you see - well that was a - that was a great - occasion. In those days you - you arranged it so you just sent out an inv}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14645256\charrsid16712901 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
tation to - some of the neighbours to come - peat cutting with you. And they all came you see and - well your - your year's supply was cut in about a day. But after that they had to be carried. And then carried - to the nearest point to the house. S
ometimes you couldn't get right to the house on account of - there being no roads or anything like that. And you had to carry them from there on your back, you see, we - we - we - most of us had - had hi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14645256\charrsid16712901 ghland ponies and - and with cree}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 lies on to carry the
 peats to the - to the nearest point, and from there, if you didn't have a road to your house you - you had to carry them on your back, that - that was part of the - as we came from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you carry sand for the floors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes. Yes. We had - I
 - I used to - go down occasionally - from the Glen to Kindisgale with the horse. It was just - well a highland pony, you know what they are. And - carry a bag of sand - for the floor.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 That house there that's there now, you helped to build that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 But the house you were in when you were a small child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Was that on the same site?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No, no, it was - further down the Glen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Can you describe it to me, what rooms it had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh well - it - it just had three rooms
, the - upper end of the - lower end as you might say, where your little kitchen work and - and sleeping quarters and another - and another - sleeping quarter as well, that was all the - it was - it was - thatched at first and then it was - turned in - it
 was felted. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 And there was a fireplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh - open fire - oh no, it was an open fireplace in the - end of the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Do you remember anybody when you were a child having the fire in the middle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, oh yes. Yes. There was - the
 - the last one I think it was in Airsary. Do you know where Airseary is? Well it's between North Bay and - as you come down from - from - Castlebay on the - east side, you come to Breiriz - and - Leerish, and - Ersary. The house I - well this place was A
uch actually. And you carry on 'til you reach North Bay, that's coming - coming north you see. That's the last house that I remember that had a fire in the middle of the - middle of the floor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 In your home did people tell stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Can you tell me something about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Well - there were - there were storytellers you know. Lots of them had - had stories - tales - that - old Fingalian tales and - and - some - tales that - that - came down - from the Arabian Nights and all these - a
ll these other tales, you see, they - they had these. And - that was - actually what was the cael - what the caelig was. Carry these stories and - songs perhaps - and - news of the place and all - all that - that was how the - the night was passed. There 
were no gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14645256\charrsid16712901 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
phones or televisions or wirelesses or anything like that at that time. Well there wasn't in either in other places.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did they do it all the year round or in the winter evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 During the winter mostly because during the summer you
 see the - the days were long and they had to work in the fields and - and - that. You see at that - that time this island was - purely crafting and fishing. There was a - this was a - a good centre for fishing, they - they used to come from all - all ove
r
 from Fraserburgh and - and - Peterhead and - Inverness, and all these fishing places. They had a season here. They - there used to be a closed time for the herrings to the tenth of May. And that was - they started on - on that date for the - for the fish
i
ng, for the herring fishing. The - the bay was at that time all - circled with - with - curing stations. And - they carried that - on until - 'til late in June I should think. The June herring here was supposed to be the best in the world then. They used 
to sell them in Russia you know as - as Baras. But - but before - they - they used to have ling fishing as well, in - in the spring. They used to cure them here. And - send them off to - to the mainland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did your father fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, he - they - it 
- it was mostly lobster fishing that he went in for. Lobster fishing and - and ling fishing, and then the herring fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What did he do in the winter months then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh well, they didn't do much - those who - who were - who were - at the herring 
fishing, they mended their nets - during the winter. The weather was - against doing anything outside, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 He didn't go away to the mainland to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Aye but - yes, he often went to Glasgow to - to labour. As a matter of fact he was killed the
re. Yes. In - in a - in one of the yards. Yes. He was a sailor in his younger days. All over the world in windjammers and - that was mostly windjammers at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did he give it up when he had a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes. Yes, oh he settled down at home, and - he used to - do lobster fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you ever go out with him fishing or help him ever with that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
I went out with some of the others, yes, yes. Oh it was a great treat for us to get a day out with - I - when I was at - a night or two or - 
a day or two at the ling fishing I was at the - at the herring fishing for - for a night or two also. Sometimes we - we got about short of sometimes, we had to return - owing to bad weather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You went with some brothers of yours did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No, no, I - I - I went with the - just the neighbours, who were - who had a boat. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 When your father was at home did he do anything to help with the domestic work of the house, like cooking or cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2058\langfe1033\langnp2058\insrsid11023910\charrsid11365698 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2058\langfe1033\langnp2058\insrsid9313509\charrsid11365698 Oh - no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Men didn't - didn't do that in - our - quarters at that time. No, no, that was - beneath their dignity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Were boys taught to cook at all when they were boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No, no. Boy - boys - didn't take anything to do - as a matter of fact it - in our quarter of - of the island, they did
n't even milk cows or anything, boys didn't, no, that was left - all left to the women. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Do you think that it differed on other parts of the island, do you think on some parts of the island men did domestic chores at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I don't think the m
en - did any domestic chores in any part of the island. No. They were - they - they were all for the outside work you see and - housework was - left entirely to the women.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 If a woman was ill after she'd had a baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, yes, oh well - that's 
- necessity as - as you might say, and - some of them could bake and some of them could - do lots of things. And of course they had to do it under these conditions. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What about the fire, who kept that going in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 The fire? Oh well - 
it's a - well known - practice - with peat fires you just - smooth them as they - as they say, just flatten down the peats, and they smoulder and - for the night and you just - built it up in the morning again you see and - and - there was no - no trouble
 in starting the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Do you remember any little rhymes or runes being said?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Yes, well - I don't know that I remember them all right. If I had access to my notes I - I - the next time you come might have. I'll prepare for you. You - you - they'
re in - they're - I think they're in cabinet against us all these - all these runes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I wondered if they were still happening when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well - very very seldom. Yes, it was only - very old people. Even - even the - the salutatio
ns coming into a house and the like of that you know - they used - they had them - in olden times. Such as - they'll come into a house and they will say - may God be here, and the - the response would be, may God be with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You remember them doing that do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Well I - I've heard of - I've heard of the expressions being used but - I can't say that - that - I actually remember hearing - the salutations themselves but - but when - from stories I have heard - I've heard these expressions being used. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 But it was getting rare when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, yes, they were getting out of use, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Were you taught to bless yourselves before food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, oh yes, my goodness, that was very important. Yes, yes. Before and after Give thanks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you all do it together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Before going to sleep at night did you have any prayers together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, well you always said your prayers in the morning and at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Was that together as a group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes
, we - yes, when - when there was a family. You say them together. Privately of course. Sometimes - these are my sheep over there, there's something disturbing them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You own all this part do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No, I don't own anything but I - I have a - I hav
e a - permission to keep my sheep over - over there and - that's part of my hobby. Yes. Yes, they're all right, they - they sometimes take runs for themselves - for no purpose at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did your father have sheep when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well - as 
a matter of fact I - I started - having sheep, I was daft on sheep when I was a little boy. And I - started building up a little flock but then I - I just left when - when - when they were - more or less established. However I started - I started right fr
o
m one. Yes. Yes, and oh I'm very fond of sheep. They're - they're - awfully nice and - I feed them during the winter you know and I've only got to whistle and they come. Yes, oh yes, they - I would stay with sheep all day. Of course I - I'm peculiar that 
way, I - I never like to see anything running away from me. I like to see them coming to me, and - I try to gain their confidence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you have a dog?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh I have - yes - just a gallivanting now - there's - there's a prodigal, you know a bitch, you
 know, and - I - I went - right over today to - to find him but - I couldn't. And he's as wise as myself. Yes. Perhaps more so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you have a dog when you were a boy too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, oh yes, I had - I had - some fine dogs, I - I like training dogs.
 And - I - I train them the way I was trained myself. It's never the stick. It's always just the word. I don't believe in taking a stick to anything. And that dog of mine, he's fourteen years - of age, and he's getting very very slow, he - he's - yes, he'
s very - and he's away after the bitches you know, and he'll come home - just crawling. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 So you were brought up yourself without the stick as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, it was a lecture. And for - far more so than a stick I can tell you, and - and - I - I was - brought up on advice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Can you tell me something about your upbringing, your parents values at that time, what did they think were the most important things in life when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh well - the most important things in life was - really Christianity. Abide by the rules of - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14645256\charrsid16712901 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 hristian religion. That was the most important things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 How did they expect you to behave towards them, your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh well - with respect. Oh yes. You - you - you - you didn't question your parents - authority. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 How did they expect you to behave towards other older people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 With great respect. Yes. Yes. You know - in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14645256\charrsid16712901 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 aelic - they use the same word to - to young people, but use the plural to old people you see. You know that? You - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 The polite form?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Yes. Yes, yes. Well - if - if - if a child was heard to use the singular to his parents - he was - just - well - to put it mildly he was badly taught.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Can you remember ever being punished for anything with a punishment as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No, I - I can honestly say that I - I was never punished. Punished with a stick or - or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 A smack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh well - I don't remember. I don't remember if I was but - but it was always the - the advice. And - and - the advice
 was sorer to me - very often than - than - than anything I could get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Can you remember anything you did that your parents did feel distressed about, what sort of thing would displease them at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh I remember one or two things that - th
at have hurt me. Through my life. I - of course this is - telling very - confidentially - talk but I - of course I was - daft about sheep and I used to look after everybody's sheep you know, and there was a man in Borre who had sheep in Valligar which is 
o
n our side of the island and I used to look after them. And - in the autumn time I thought it - this lamb was - it was time to - to - take him away from its mother you see, and I - I came home from school and there was nobody in. And so off I went to the 
h
ill with the dog, you see. And - I took thinks - sheep. And I drove it - from Valligar right down to Borve - and - delivered it to its owner. And I got home - it was pretty dark - and by that time my mother was - up on the hills - looking for me, she thou
g
ht when - when I wasn't home and when - the - the dog wasn't home - I must be in trouble when - when - I didn't turn up. I could - could hear her call, it's only that just about - broke my heart. Yes, I remember. Oh well I suppose there were other things 
that - were as important, but - that - really - stayed with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Her distress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Yes, yes. I - she was a - getting an old woman at that time, well - not old as - as they term them nowadays but - searching for me and I was all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Who took the main share in your upbringing, was it your mother or your father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh it was my mother, oh yes, it was always the mother. Always the mother that brings up children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you go regularly to church in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes. Very - very - very
 much so, I - on the - of course I used to go to - to church every morning because - I was a - an altar clerk you see. And I used to go to church every morning, and then - on Sundays - it was church in the morning, evening service at night and - Sunday sc
hool, I used to - to teach Sunday school. I was - I was a pupil teacher for - for a year before I left you see, I - I - was connected with it that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 At Christmas time can you remember what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh well - we - we - always went to midnight mass you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Children too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, every - everybody - didn't matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Even quite young children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, yes. Yes, oh they went to - to Christmas - midnight mass. And - on - on Easter morning - well - of course - we had a tradition tha
t - on Easter morning you know, the - the sun rose and it used to dance about - for joy. We - we - used to climb the Ben Hearal and - watch the sun rise. Oh, we - we didn't sleep that night, we - we - we stayed up all night until it was - four or five in 
the morning, then we - we used to - to go up Ben Heaver and watch the sun rise, of course - I don't know whether it danced or not but - our eyes were weary in any case - for want of sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 In those days did you have to bed in bed by a certain time when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes. My goodness. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Can you tell me something about bedtime procedure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh bed - oh well about ten o'clock I should think was - was the - standard time for getting to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Summer and winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Summer - no, 
summer and winter, yes. Oh we - we never stayed late. If there was a cailey in the house you might be allowed to - to stay for a little while longer you know, but - but - we never had the - the caileys they have - there you see - I'm up at eight o'clock e
very morning. The people of this place - nowadays they're less - I don't know what they get up. But - of course I was at that all my life. Getting up at eight o'clock, well I - I'm ready to get up, I don't want to stay in bed any longer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 When you were a child did all the children sleep in one room or in separated halves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well - the - they separated them the best way they could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You were saying they separated the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, the best way - well - you know - with the - some childre
n they - they would put four in bed. Two at each end. That was all right for children, like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Was it a box bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes. They were all box beds in - in my younger days. Very - very useful really because - they had a roof you know. But - that the
 - the drips - coming off the the roof. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 So if the grown ups were sitting up talking in your house would there be children asleep in the same room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well not in the same room. The - if the grown ups were talking they would be in the kitchen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 That's where they would sit would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, that's where they - where they would sit, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Because that had the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, that's right, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you have to wash your feet before you went to bed and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh - well often it was very necessary. As - while we were - staying - it was all mud of course. It's - it's different sands, you don't get the sand off very easily but - mud you can - but - oh I lose the thread of my story occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You went about barefoot in the summer months did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Yes, yes. Oh it would be a disgrace for us to go - with shoes - in the summer time. Yes. Oh you - oh you were weak. Yes, you were weak if you had shoes on during the - as a matter of fact we couldn't afford them in any case. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you ever get paid for anything you did to help, neighbours errands or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh we wouldn't dare to take payment. Oh no my goodness no. It would be a disgrace - to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14645256\charrsid16712901  take payment for - for any act}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901  of - charity as you might say. Well I'm the same way yet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Do you think there's been a change in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh - a great big change, you can't get anything for nothing nowadays. In here. Och they've - well - I'll draw a blind over that. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Do you remember your mother ever being helped by the neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh yes, oh yes, she - she helped the neighbours a great deal and the neighbours helped her, yes, all the - they were all for helping one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 They never paid each other for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2058\langfe1033\langnp2058\insrsid11023910\charrsid11365698 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2058\langfe1033\langnp2058\insrsid9313509\charrsid11365698 Oh no. No. NO. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 But - if there was a - a - a friend of theirs who - who - was badly off they - they would give them a day's work and pay them for it so you see. Yes, to help them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Who looked after the hens, did you have hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Hens? Yes, we had hens, I - of course hens don't - need looking - like so many after you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Just the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, just the food. And - put them away to somewhere where they don't - spoil the corn or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Was it the women who looked after the hens or the men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Ah well - the women and - and the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 That wasn't men's work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 That - no, no, that wasn't men's work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 In your family did your mother do any planting?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, they - yes, we - as a matter of fact we still do it here - I do the lazy beds and - Peggy just does the planting. Yes, oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 That's another tradition is it, the women planting the lazy beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, oh yes. Of course - I suppose men do it also but - it's mostly a woman's job. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 In the social life at that time, the caileys and that sort of thing, was it mixed groups of men and women sitting together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, yes, oh yes. Yes. You see, there were - certain - known story tellers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Were there in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Aye 
- aye - no, I can't say that there were. But - if you got a hold of one of these old men you know and - for a cailey one night well - the others would gather in you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would word spread round by word of mouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, oh yes. Bush telephone. Yes. Or at least they - they might see him going there - if it was - sufficient.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Could your father read and write easily, I know a lot of people of that generation couldn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, my father could read and - could write a good letter, he was - h
e was the youngest - the youngest - of fourteen. And - he had a - certain amount of education. Yes, he could write a nice letter. But my mother couldn't. My mother was the only daughter - in the family you see, and she was about - perhaps two or three day
s at school - but - she always - told us - they had a book, and - the biggest word in the book was opportunity, and she could spell that word until her last days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did she like reading, did she ever read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 She didn't read at all, no, no, but - oh she understood a lot of - things that she heard. Oh she had - she had very good }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14645256\charrsid16712901 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
aelic too. I - I - I taught in - evening classes in Edinburgh for twenty-seven years. And - well when I had to go - to the grammar you know, I - I can honestly say that there w
ere very few words that I had to change - in my own - vocabulary. She - she - she - she had perfect English yes, and - it's a wonderful thing you know that - they - they had an interest in their language. And - if you said any word that was - that was out
 of - out of the gramm}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14645256\charrsid16712901 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 r - principles she would - soon correct you. Oh you - you were very stupid.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did she speak English at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No, she didn't speak English, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did your father speak English?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh he - oh my father could speak good English yes. Yes, oh he was all over the world you know. Sailing. Yes, and - and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you ever get any pocket money when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 There was - one day in the year the - the mascot day or - the fair day as they called it, and - well - w
e generally made a point of earning - about the sixpence that day - shearing sheep or something like that for others you know. Aye, that was our pocket money for the year. Oh we - we - we never got pocket money. No, no. No, that was unthinkable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 In the Glen and Castlebay who were considered to be the most important people at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes. I - oh I suppose the merchants were the - great people at that time, yes. I should think so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Were they Catholics or Protestants at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
All mixed. Yes. Yes. Away in the street down there, there was one Protestant and the rest were Catholics, yes. Yes. But - that didn't make any difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 There wasn't any religious friction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No. No, there wasn't really. We seemed to keep the balance properly here. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Can you tell me how you were expected to behave in those days at a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You said your grace didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, yes, oh yes, we - had to - say your grace and take - whatever was put in front of you. Y
ou couldn't say, oh I don't like that and I don't like this. There wasn't such a thing, you had to take what you got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What happened if you left your food and said, I don't want to eat this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well you - you just had to do without it. You know, th
e - children that are spoilt that way nowadays. Yes. Oh - I - I don't think we ever refused anything, we - there was - many a thing we didn't like. But - we had to take it all the same. We - of course we - we preferred - loaf bread to - to oatcakes. But -
 loaf bread - well it came in - came by the road on Friday and we had it for Sunday you see. But the rest was scones - scones and - and oat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14645256\charrsid16712901 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 bread. The same with porridge. We - we often had the porridge at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 At tea time was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Not at - at 
- at night - at suppertime, yes. And - of course there was - the milk was scarce. We used to have it with treacle at times and - and - we didn't like it but we had to take it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14645256\charrsid16712901 
. You see - youngsters are pamp}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 ered nowadays. Oh - yes, they are pampered, oh yes, oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 And they're not happier for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No. Oh no, they're not, no. My goodness, we hadn't a grouse in the world. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Could you talk at the meal table, chat among yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, yes. Yes, we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Ah we never did. No, they gave us exactly. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Were they particular about you held your implements you ate with, your spoon and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh no, well - you see - forks and knives were - weren't generally in use - that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Was there a spoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh yes, there was always a spoon but - you see, potatoes they - they were - baked in their jackets and - we wouldn't - dare say, I don't like this and I don't like that. If it was put down for you - well you just had to - 
that was your - that was your meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Knives and forks were not common then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
No, no they weren't common. You - you were - the potatoes were boiled in their jackets you see and - and the fish - which was the - we - we didn't - have - much meat, onl
y on special occasions that we had meat you see. People were very poor. And - you just ate it the best way you could. Perhaps - perhaps there might be a knife and fork for a - for a meat - for a meat - meal.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Was that your own mutton usually that it would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Mm hm. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 When the potatoes were boiled?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did they have any custom here of not liking the pot to go dry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 They weren't worried about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No. No, they - well of course it - it was never allowed to go dry, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you have your own plates or did you have it out of a common one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh we - well there was a - there was a big dishful of potatoes you see, then you had your own plate for - for your meal you see, just - helped yourself - off this - off the common - the common - tray you see, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 In the Shetland Islands some of the older people just ate off the one tray without their own plates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Was that the custom on Barra do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well -
 no, I shouldn't think - I think they had - they always had a - had a - had a plate, but - off the common - off the common tray, yes. There was a - a big wooden tray made for the potatoes. Of course - we take much - much more potatoes in the islands - in 
Barra here anyway, than - than they take on the mainland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 And less bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Beg pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Less bread here than on the mainland do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I should think so, yes, yes. Yes. Oh we - we - we like our potatoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 When you had porridge was that out of a bowl, your mother gave you each your own bowl did she?
\par 
