\insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 h, she says, people talking about bringing up families nowadays, it's not the mothers that bring up th
e families, she said, it's the grandmothers. It's quite true. She says, I remember your grandfather's house, she says, when I saw eighteen people sitting down to table. Yes. He - your grandfather has four - had fourteen children of his own, and she says, 
