\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 So he would do a bit of work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh he did a lot of - curing of the ling. A lot of that. Curing of the ling and - of course they sent them away. Different parts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Were there any other jobs that he would do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
I don't - I don't remember - I remember him - him being at the - ling, curing. Remember that, but my father was quite young when he died. Only about forty-five I think or something like that.
 We had a croft - the - our croft was - behind the house here, and - we had cows and we had a horse and - take home the peat with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 He would spend a lot of time working on the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh he'd spend a lot of time working the croft. Autumn time you 
grew all your own hay and - barley and - all that sort of thing. And - cutting peats and - a lot of work. Keep the place going for the winter, you know, you did all that in the - the spring, summer. Then carry them home and - build up the stacks and have 
your fuel for the winter. Right on all the winter until the next spring again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would you girls have to help on the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh well - we used to milk the cows. I've never milked a cow in my life. Never milked a cow but - my mother was the one that 
did the milking because the cow knew her, And my eldest sister too, she could milk her without any bother, but the rest of us - the cow wouldn't let them near her. And you had to sing to the cow you know, before she'd give you the milk. Yes. They always s
ang to the cows.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you have any regular tasks yourself in the home that you were expected to carry out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh yes, we - carried in the water, there was no running water in those days, we had to go to the well. Get the water for - cooking - and drinking and - then we used the burn water for washing up. That sort of thing. But we were always near a burn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You would have the washday down by the burn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes. Yes. Build a fire down there and - big fire and - take your tubs down and have a right
 good - picnic down there. It was very - it was - lovely you know on a nice day, washing the blankets - and - getting into the tub with your feet and stamping them and - quite nice. It wasn't a bad life really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did your mother spend her whole time working in the home and on the croft or did she also go out to earn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh no, she had plenty to do at home, brought up a family and - she had the croft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Do you know if she ever went with the herring fishing before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No, she was - in her own home. Her own place, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 There weren't any other relatives living in the house besides yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2058\langfe1033\langnp2058\insrsid11023910\charrsid11365698 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2058\langfe1033\langnp2058\insrsid9313509\charrsid11365698 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would your father help with looking after you as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 My father was very handy. He could do anythi
ng, my father was very musical. He could play anything. Play the pipes, play the fiddle - even play the tin whistle. He was a - very wonderful - piper. And play the violin. And mother used to compose songs. Yes. Yes. Oh while you wait she'll get a song ab
out you. Yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would you have sort of musical evenings then as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh yes, all the time. We had a big fire here, huge big fire and - and the - we had the paraffin lamps in those days, and - this was a great cailey house, people used t
o come caelying here. And - they'd turn down the lamp, just a wee bit of the - the light, and only the light of the fire and told ghost stories and all that sort of thing. Oh they had - we had - I remember - that quite well, I remember people coming in an
d telling the - tales you know, stories, skelochan they called them. And we would be just all ago you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 The children would listen too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well the eldest of the children would sit up. Remember I used to sit up. But the rest didn't, the youngest
 children went to bed. But this went on - oh - all the time I was young. Storytelling - from house to house. They would pick a house you know and go to such and such a house one night and - they would all come in and - and there was one storyteller that -
 he was very popular. It was a great time, soon as ever got it dark and after they had their evening - suppers, the - after six o'clock they'd - all congregate together and - tell stories the whole night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would you all sing in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh there'd be singing too, yes. There'd be singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would there be any refreshments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh yes, there was always tea of course. Just tea. Oh there wasn't - in those days people didn't drink whisky the way drink it now at all. I remember when I went t
o Fort William I was quite - I wasn't very old, I was just about fifteen, and a thing that shocked me more than anything was to see a woman drunk. That was terrible. People didn't drink - especially women never drank - when I was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 They wouldn't be allowed in the bar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Well they would never dream of going inside the bar, they would never - terrible insult if you went to the bar. People all - they would have looked down at you. They'd be shocked to see a woman going into the bar. That was her 
character finished. She was done for. How the world has changed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would your father help with things like putting the children to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I don't think so, that was a - woman's job. Men didn't do that until just recently. No. No. They never did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would he ever take you out by yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Well I'm not very sure really. I can't remember that. But I know they wouldn't put them to bed or anything like that, no. Or wash them or - bath them at night, they would never do that. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Could you tell me the sort of typical day's food, the sort of food you ate at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Well, we always - we had our own sheep and we always had - they killed at certain times of the year you know. And - they made the - puddings, you know, the - the i
nside they used to make black puddings and - they had the tripe and they had - the inside and then - what they couldn't use they salted it and used it - later on. There were no fridges in those days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 So you would have meat quite often would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Yes, we had meat - we always had plenty of fish. Fresh fish, funny - we all liked fish. We loved fresh fish. Even better than the meat. We got a lot of - during the summer the - it was a big - the - the herring industry was here was - very ripe a
nd - there's always lovely herring, you know, beautiful herring, you never tasted anything like them. I can taste them yet, you know, what I mean coming back from the holiday, and - I - never tasted herring like them. Great big fat - lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 So you would eat the fish mainly in the summer then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 And have a bit of the salt meat in the winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What about vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 We had several - well we used - oh yes, we grow our own vegetables, we used to grow - cabbage and - and 
the - we used to have the loveliest parsley, you never saw anything like it, used to be - at the back there, the cabbage and carrots too, we grew very good carrots and turnips and - kale. Kale, do you know what a kale is. Curly kale, mm hm, yes. Mm hm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What about any tinned food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh that was - never heard of, nobody -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Not corned beef for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No. No, not even corned beef, not to my knowledge anyway, never saw it in the house un my life. Preferred the fresh food. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, rabbits too. There was always rabbits, you could get a lot of rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you eat the birds, sea birds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, they used to - I don't remember eating them myself but - they used to eat - what do they call them - scarts is it? Skarts,
 they used to eat them. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Well, we didn't have - we didn't have - the like - loaf, she didn't make a loaf, but she made all oat cakes, and scones. She was a lovely baker my mother. Pan cakes and things. That sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 She made jam sometimes, made rhubarb jam, yes. We had rhubarb out there too. She made jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Any pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No. They didn't believe in pickles you know, no. No, they didn't - they didn't think vin - vinegar was good for you. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Was there any bottling at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Any what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Bottling of vegetables, when you put the vegetables in a bottle for the winter, a vacuum bottle? I think it probably started after the first war. You don't remember that anyway. And she didn't make any wines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
No. But my sisters used to make wine. She did, I came across her cooking book there and I had the - she used to make lots of wine, she used to make - rhubarb wine, and - rowan. Rowan. And - what's the o
ther thing - well she made lots of different wine. And very good I can remember - tasted quite good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would you have some wine at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes. Christmas was a great time. Oh yes, Christmas they went all out to have - everything
 for Christmas. They used to make a lot of - dumpling you know. Big crootie dumplings you know - great big crootie - you put them in a cloth, they called them crootie dumplings, they don't make them nowadays. In a big big pot. And - put them in all - like
 
a like a Christmas cake, you know, the mixture of a Christmas cake, and if you - mixed it maybe with ale or - plenty eggs in it and all kinds of fruit that - that you could get. We always had plenty of fruit when nobody else had it because - we had a brot
h
er in Australia, and they always sent - always fruit coming. Always fruit. Sultanas and all kinds of - raisins and - they'd make that and they'd put it in a cloth, then boil it in a pot. Then you could eat it hot or cold. Slice it down just like a cake wh
en it was cold. I call that crootie dumpling.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Is sounds delicious?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
It was - delicious, it really was. My sister still makes them - she still makes them, this family was so fond of them. In fact when they went away to school they used to send the
m - dumplings - now and again you know, because the - made them feel more at home with having a dumpling - sent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you have porridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes. Oh we always had porridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you have porridge and milk for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Porridge and milk fo
r breakfast, yes, always. Sometimes porridge at night. In the wintertime. If you had a cold or anything like that they believed in porridge for your chest, it was good for the chest. Uh huh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would you all sit at the table together for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 It wasn't a case of sort of coming and going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
No, no, no. Well you see they - as the family grew they went away from home. They went away from home as they grew up. And there wasn't always - there was only about - there wouldn't be - more than three at - at home at a time after they grew up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Your brother was saying that he never remembered being smacked for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No, I don't think they smacked them at all. No, I don't think they - they checked them. And they didn't - r
aise their voices to them, I never - can never - I know that my father never raised his voice to us. And mother maybe if she was angry she would - raise her voice, but she never spanked them. She corrected us. But she says now - that's very wrong. If you 
do it again you'll be severely punished. But she - my father never - he was such a gentle man, never raised his voice. But mother was the one really that ruled the family yes. Mother.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What sort of things did they emphasise as being important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Well, good manners, especially. That was most important, to be polite to your elders. And not to speak back to your elders. Never to speak back. You weren't allowed to speak back. Cheeky you know what }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2844349\charrsid16712901 I mean? Never allow that. And o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 h, I suppose I don't know - I don't know. But - I don't remember being ever spanked. Either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did they teach you to behave to your brothers and sisters in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes. Yes. Oh that was understood. That was understood, I remember Callum pulling my hair
 once. And my mother hadn't been well at all and - oh I don't know he wanted something that I had and - I didn't want to give it to him and I had very long hair and right down - and he pulled my hair and there was a - a woman, a neighbour - she was - in, 
s
he was looking after my mother, mother was in bed, and I was just a kid, I don't know how - I don't know if I was in school even. Callum would be just maybe three or so. Anyway he pulled my hair. And instead of spanking Callum, this lady spanked me. For d
aring to - well - going against Callum you know - I should haven him a - maybe a - whatever we had, we were arguing about it and - she thought that he should - be the one that should have it - have it. Remember that. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 If another child hit you did they say you should hit back or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Well - not in our family because he was the only boy at home. As you ever - the only boy - there were so many girls, we - we never hit back, we never - no. Different with girls. If there were boys I suppose they wou
ld tell them to - defend themselves. I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 If you had any worries would you feel able to talk to your mother about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 She was quite an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, oh yes. But if we - if we got spanked in
 school, if we got the cane, you know, sometimes we did, and - we were terrified mother would know about it because she said, you must have been misbehaving or you wouldn't have got the cane. She wouldn't take our part, she would - be quite annoyed becaus
e we misbehaved in school. Thought that was very wrong. We were quite right to get the cane. And I would be terrified they would tell on us that we were spanked in school. We never told - if we - if the - we were spanked in school we never let on at home.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would you say your father was easier to talk to or less that your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh my father was - yes, he was - he - he was - really he was - I never met anybody like him, he was - so gentle. Very very gentle, a lovely man. Uh huh. Kind and gentle and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did he show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Yes. Oh he was very kind. Of course somebody had to be hard you know. 'Cos children, they want their own way as you know with having a family yourself. So if children want their own way, well - you didn't our own way, 
we just had to do what we were told. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you have any celebrations at a birthday at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Birthdays? Yes. Oh yes, something special - extra, you know, maybe something. Very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Presents of some kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What sort of presents might you get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh I - I can't remember now but - wouldn't be very much. No. Can't remember, but there was always a - - perhaps you would have special tea or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 With some friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, children of our own age
 you know. Children round about, the neighbours, but - there weren't a lot of children round - about us. At the time, no. When we came here we were the only family up here, there weren't any of these houses - built even. We were the first up here. Then th
e other people started to come up. Because our croft was up here, we were - living away from the croft. Then we built this house, we - had to build it on the croft to be nearer. The cattle were at the back there and the croft's over the hill there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 It's the other side of the hill is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 It's up on the slope of the hill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Not the other side?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Over the hill there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 It's on this side of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, yes, yes, sort of back of the house there. You had to climb the wee hill up there to get to it. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2058\langfe1033\langnp2058\insrsid11023910\charrsid11365698 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2058\langfe1033\langnp2058\insrsid9313509\charrsid11365698 No. No, no. No, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh no. We were very meek and mild, we had to be. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well we played all our games outside, we never played games in the house, it was all - by the time we came in we were ready for bed.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What sort of games would you play as a girl then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh we'd play - lots and lots of games, ring a ring o' roses, I can remember th
at. London Bridge had broken down. And skipping - skipping. Whatever game was in - fashionable at the time, we played it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Marbles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Don't remember - mar - oh yes, rather yes, we played that a lot. We played them outside with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2844349\charrsid16712901 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901  chuckies you know with wee stones. Pebbles, mm hm. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What about reading, were there books in the house to read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Books, oh - house was always full of books, my si}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2844349\charrsid16712901 
ster was - she was a great folklor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 ist, and - s
he was teaching in the school you know, and - she - knew - everybody used to come up here for information, just like yourself, Mrs Kennedy Fraser, have you heard of Mrs Kennedy Fraser? She was a collector of folk songs, she was - and - books, the house wa
s full of books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 They were your sister's books mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes. My sister's books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would she read to the family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No she didn't read to the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 There was no reading aloud then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, she'd - oh no - no reading aloud, no, no, didn't read aloud, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did the family take any newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
I suppose there'd be newspapers of the time, I can't remember but of course - into the house, of course there would be, I can't even remember how often the boat came in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I think there was a weekly one which some people got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh there was a weekly - there was a weekly one -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Highland News or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh I - yes, maybe, I don't remember anything about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Certainly there weren't daily papers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes. There would
n't be daily papers because the boat only came - I think the boat came in three times a week. Monday, Wednesday and Friday. That was before the planes started coming in. And you got the papers then. Not daily papers, the Oban Times at the weekend anyway. 
Oban Times and - I think that was all the papers that - I remember anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I don't suppose you ever want away on a family holiday, you wouldn't have been able to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2058\langfe1033\langnp2058\insrsid11023910\charrsid11365698 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2058\langfe1033\langnp2058\insrsid9313509\charrsid11365698 No. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Nobody observed bank holidays here did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No. No, we 
had holidays, we had church holidays which was - observed very very - carefully, mm, all the shops were shut and - nobody ever did any work. Never - Nobody ever did anything at all, inside or outside, well inside, yes, maybe but - they would never do a wa
shing or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did your parents think it wrong to work on a Sunday then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh they never worked on a Sunday except what was necessary. Except what was - they would never dream of doing anything - on a Sunday except just the food and - that was all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 But you could play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I think - yes, I think so. We went to church three times a day. There wasn't much time. Much - chance to play games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 So you went three times, you went to the morning Mass and then the Sunday school and then Benediction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You weren't in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I wasn't in the choir, no, I've no voice at all for singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Were there any other sort of church activities then that you joined in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did your mother and father both manage to get to church or did your mother stay behind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh no, no, everybody went to church - there were only two Masses - and when the children were young somebody stayed in. They didn't tae the children to church not when they were babies. Because I think it's awful, crying babi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180291\charrsid16712901 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
s in church. It's just terrible and I'm very glad - they do it on the mainland you know, - they do it in Glasgow, screeching - kids all the time, it doesn't matter what Mass you go to. And I always say well surely
 somebody could stay at home and go to the next one. But - no, somebody stayed - somebody went to the early mass and - then they came home, we had our breakfast, after the early mass. Then the rest of us went to the eleven o'clock mass and the one that wa
s
 the - if the children weren't able to go, when they were babies, but - somebody stayed at home to look after them. Not necessarily my father, could have been anybody. Any of the rest of the family, the bigger girls you know. Mm hm. But they never bought 
- brought babies in arms to church like what-they do today. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Do you know whether your father took any interest in politics at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I don't - I don't - know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You don't remember any talk in the family about politics anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What about the land leaguing, was he interested in that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 In what?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 The land leaguing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes. I - I don't know. My father was so musical you know, if he had any spare time at all he was playing the fiddle or playing the pip
es or - playing even a tin whistle. He could play anything, he was very very musical.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did your mother have any interests like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Spinning and carding and weaving and - that was my mother's interests, she - she we - she spun every - all the wo
ol that was used for stockings or - we all had to have hand knitted stockings in those days, the boys and the girls. It was hand knitted stockings, and she used to card and - and spin all the wool - from her own sheep you know. And then dye the colours wh
atever colour she - wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would she ever go out just to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
No. No such a thing as women enjoying themselves in those days. No. They were too busy with their families and their croft. They hadn't time to do anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 There weren't any sort of sports that one could take part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
No I don't think so. No. Don't think so. But - they came to the house, they had caileys in the house you know, that was - their - their only recreation really, and that was their way. They didn't go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Do you think your mother and father shared the same friends or did they have separate ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh no, they shared the same friends. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Were there any sort of savings clubs, like a sick club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I don't - I don't remember that, no. Don't remember that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What was your mother's attitude if you got dirty when you were out playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I think she thought it was - healthy to get - fall out and get dirty. You fell out and - she didn't - she didn't scold us for getti
ng dirty or anything torn, no. She thought it was healthy like - it wasn't - she said it's better that than wearing the sheets. She used to say that. Better that - than wearing the s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid662945\charrsid16712901 h}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 eets. She meant that - being in bed ill you know. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 So she encouraged you to get out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh we were always out, were never in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 If she was ill in bed who would help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well my sisters were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You wouldn't have anyone from outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, oh yes, indeed. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Were there other relatives who would come in and help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes. The relatives would - even the neighbours, they would - they would come in and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Do you feel there was a lot of helping at that time then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What sort of ways would people help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh they helped on
e another, didn't matter - there was anybody - poorly, everybody helped, everybody went and everybody brought them - something nice you know that - if there was anything special they had, if they just churn - made a churning of fresh butter they would bri
n
g them - fresh butter or - everybody had their own cows in those days. They had their butter, we used to have - big crock of butter, I can remember it, we had - big brown crock of butter and mother used to - have it full for the winter, and they pickled i
t with the course salt you know. And - oh I can taste that butter yet, it was gorgeous, on oatcake. Was just lovely. Made our own chees}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid662945\charrsid16712901 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 , and crowdie and all that sort of thing, made that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would one family lend things to another family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Well anything, if you wanted to cut the grass and you didn't have a scythe well so and so's got a scythe and you gust got the loan of it. That sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Quite a difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Quite different, yes, yes, quite
 different. Oh you were never stuck. If there was a widow and she hadn't - anyone to - bring her - fish maybe you know, the - everybody used to bring her fish, she had more fish than anybody else - in the end because everybody was bringing a share.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You were brought up to give to the poorer people were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 The poorest people were mainly the very old were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Very old, yes. The very old or people that were - maybe bedridden or - or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 There wasn't any sort of pride felt or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
I think - I think there was - what did they call it in those days, I don't know - that is - I - I - I know there were people who getting parish relief. Yes, yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Do you think that was thought to be rather a disgrace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Very degrading believe me, they would rather have starved than - some people would Willingly starve rather than - sort of begging you know. Wouldn't have that at all, they were very proud.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did people just drop in casually or did they have to be invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh dropped in cas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid662945\charrsid16712901 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901  - nobody was ever invited. Door was always open just turn the - turn the knob and walk in, nobody ever knocked at a door. Just walked in. Anybody in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 There is a bar down there in the town, would the men go down in the evenings at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
The bar was down - at the pier in those days. I suppose the fishermen you know if they had been out - for maybe a week or so at sea when they come home they probably would go in there and get a dram. I don't remember ever seeing
 anybody drunk - in my young days, never. That was the first time I ever saw a drunk when I saw a woman. In Fort William and I - couldn't - couldn't get over it. I just - couldn't get over it. That was awful, a woman getting drunk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Your father wasn't temperance though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 He would sometimes have a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
No, I don't think he ever did. No, I don't think he ever did. Don't think he ever did, I don't think my father was - ever in the bar. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You know that you have certain ways here of showing courtesy in the language don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Who would you say the more polite version to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well, you'd say - you never said you to a person older than yourself. Never say you. We'd say it in gael - I - I can't - explain it
 in English. You understand. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 But that was mainly for your elders, what about the minister and the priests and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, oh you always say - you always spoke very politely to them. Always, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 And the merchants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh the mercha
nts - I don't - I wouldn't - I wouldn't be very polite to some of the merchants myself today believe me. Oh they're terrible - you know - do you know what that girl charged me for coming up? She took \{BLANK\}
 she charged me seven bob. She did indeed. I near
ly dropped. Seven bob. Isn't that shocking. You've just got to - you've just got to - pay it out, what can you do. But they're just - they're such a greedy lot. And they just give you what - they have, they don't give you what you want, they give you just
 what they have, take it or leave it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You think they've changed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Changed, of course they've changed. Changed. Out of all recognition, believe me
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What were they like when you were young then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh, they were different altogether, you know, just like everybody else, they were different altogether, they were very -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would they have been more helpful to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 They did, I'm sure they did. As far as I can remember them they were - such nice gentlemen, they were really gentlemen. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 So you would respect them when you were younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, you would respect them, you'd respect anybody older than yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 And the schoolmaster would be another person?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes. Yes. They de - deserved respect you know. They were - that type of person too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Do you know the phrase a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Can you think of anyone here that you would have called that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Today? Do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No, when you were young, before the first war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh - oh yes, there was a lot of - nature's own gentlemen. Was a lot of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Anyone that comes to mind though in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh they're all dead now of course. But - there were - I could mention a few, they're all dead now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 But when you say they're nature's own gentlemen what was it about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well the way they acted you know, the way they behaved and the way they spoke to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Sort of civility you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Was there a policeman around at all in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No, there wasn't a policeman in those days, not in my days. There was no policeman at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you ever see anything of the landlord, that was Lady Gordon Cathcart wasn't it
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes. I never met her at all, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Do you remember there ever being somebody in the
 district who was disapproved of and the people showed their disapproval in some sort of obvious way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I don't remember the - anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 In England we have something called rough music when people go and bang kettles outside a house. There's nothing like that you remember?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Or not speaking to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You don't think people would do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would they be more to learnt do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes. I think everyone got on very well together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you feel your parents had a struggle to make ends meet when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well I suppose they had. Quite sure they had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 But you didn't feel that at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No, no, we never felt - but I'm sure they must have. 
Sure they must bringing up a big family, but we had a good croft, you know what I mean, we had always - plenty of milk, we had our own milk and we had our butter and we had our eggs. We had our mutton, we had our sheep. And if we were never - we were neve
r
 hungry or - we never looked for anything out of the shops you know what I mean, cakes and that we never had them. We had plenty - we had oatcakes and scones. And pancakes and - and for other cakes we - we never - thought of them. Never had them. Never ha
d
 them. We got a lot out of the sea. We got an awful lot out of the sea, we used to get a lot of fun out of the - we used to gather dulse and we loved to eat dulse Off the rocks you know, it grows on the rocks. Almost - a kind of seaweed I suppose, and the
n you know the long ste}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid662945\charrsid16712901 am}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 y things. Do you call it - rock -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Not Iris?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh I don't know the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Is it a seaweed or a flower?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No, no, it's - a stalk, like rhubarb. Crows in the sea, you get it when the tide is out. Well we used to - get that
. It had a - big leaf, just like a - a rhubarb stalk for all the world. And dark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 And you'd eat that would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh we loved it, yes, it was lovely. Used to cut it up and pretend it was black striped balls. Oh full of iodine it must have been awf
ully good for us. Must have been when you think of it, all that - used to love that, nobody goes to gather dulse now. No. No, but we did, that was - that's what we did - between Sunday school and evening service, went over to the other side and got it. An
d
 - we used to get cockles galore. Loved cockles, we - loved anything out of the sea. Used to love it. The clams, you know, the lovely - you know the clams. Have you tasted them? They're lovely, I love them, I love anything out of the sea. Liked all the - 
p
rawns and all that sort of stuff. Oh we used to get lots of things out of the sea. And we knew where to get them and - even the - limpets. Used to get these and boil them and - eat them, fry them with a bit of butter - salt butter in a pan. They were deli
cious. We never missed the sweets, we never got sweets. Except just on a rare occasion, you know. Uh huh.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did your parents try to teach you the alphabet or anything before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did they take an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh yes. Mm hm. Taught us our prayers. Taught us that - religiously. But - of course my mother didn't go to school really, she was born in Lingley. Don't think she was very long in school. She couldn't read or write - except }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15877612\charrsid16712901 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 aelic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would your father go up and meet the schoolteachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would he go up to the school and meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh they - they didn't do that in those days, no. Didn't do that in those days at all. They didn't do that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you enjoy the school yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Not particularly, I wasn't - the clever one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You weren't sorry when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No I wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Was that at fourteen you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, fourteen, you were allowed to leave then. My great interest was cooking in those 
days, I loved - cooking, I was terribly keen on cooking, learning how to cook properly. That was my greatest interest.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you go to the evening classes in cooking then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, and school here, but - when I went away I was very keen to learn - al
l about cooking. Oh yes, went to evening classes on - cookery, we had a cookery teacher that taught - cookery and - was terribly interested in cooking. All sorts of cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Was that why you decided to get this job then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Could you tell me how you got that job in Fort William?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Well I got the job because - I was so keen on cookery. And to learn how to do the thing right, and - there was a - a priest here, and I went to see him. And I told him, and asked him if he could get me a
 job. And he did. Got me a job. With a friend of his, she was a relation - who had a big house in Fort William. And - she was - a famous - cook, she was wonderful, do you know everybody - knew about her. And - I stayed four years there. And - then - this 
p
riest had gone - he had been here, he had been in Spain. He was a professor in Spain. And - he - he was sent over, he was sent to Barra you know, and the contrast was - got him down, he was ill for a long time. And - he went away to the Canary Islands, he
 was there for three years, he'd only half a lung. And - then he came - he came back and - he got the parish and - Rirrot, that's outside Oban, and that's where I landed. It was he who - sent me away to begin with. And I was forty-two years with him.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Were you the housekeeper there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I was the housekeeper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Were there any other people helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Yes, yes, there was a curate and - I'd two girls - helping me. I did the cooking and I looked after the house. And we used to - Fry the eggs in olive oil and honey, that's the way they had them in - in Spain. He used to get his eggs fried - in olive}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15877612\charrsid16712901  oil and honey, did you ever go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 t - eggs - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 So he didn't have t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15877612\charrsid16712901 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 pical Scottish food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, oh yes, oh yes. Oh yes, but that was just the eggs. That's the way he liked the eggs done. I always cooked with oil, olive oil. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would he have roasts and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, yes, oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Very different from what you'd had here anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes. But that's the - sort of thing I like doing. Mm hm. Like cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Could you tell me a typical meal in the house that you would cook for him then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Typical meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Typical day's meals you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well - we always had - there was always - soup - and two or three vegetab
les and potatoes, and always a sweet and cheese, biscuits and cheese and fruit and coffee we always had that every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Wines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, they'd have wine - sauterne you know the wine, yes, always had imported - white wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would he entertain for dinner parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Yes, he entertained an awful lot, it was an open door. People used - during the war people used to come, we had - I had a lot of hens, I used to keep my own hens, and we were very lucky - we knew all the tradesmen, you know, the shop
keepers, and - I could get anything, I was never hard up for anything. I would always; get - any - you had your - ration cards, I never had - for - would get any amount of butcher meat, knew the butchers. And there were - there - he was in such respect, h
e
ld in such respect, and they knew that he entertained an awful lot, I could get a roast of mutton or roast of beef anytime. And before the war - well - when we knew the war was on I got - a - chest of tea home, and - two bags of sugar and I was able to ma
ke my jam, my own jam, all during the war. We had a lot of fruit in the garden, I used.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you do the home baking too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I - I did the home baking, yes. I did. Uh huh, it was very interesting. And I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What sort of people would come to dinner then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh clergy. Only the clergy. Oh he didn't have - just the clergy. They were passing through and you know Fort William was just in the centre there, passing through. They would land in at any time. We could always give them a meal. Always had plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did he give you a separate room where you could sit down and so on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, I had my own - sitting room, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 So you were really quite independent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 He didn't expect to know where you were if you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2058\langfe1033\langnp2058\insrsid11023910\charrsid11365698 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2058\langfe1033\langnp2058\insrsid9313509\charrsid11365698 No, no. No, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 But I always told him if I was going to be out late I always said I was going to be out late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Was that different to the first place you went to, were there more staff at the first place? You went first to Fort William I think you s
aid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 And then back to Oban?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 When you were at Fort William how many were there in the household there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Just the - two clergy, two. And the two maids. Just two maids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 So it was really quite similar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes, just the same, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 How did they address you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Miss Johnston, yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What sort of life did you have - how often in fact were you able to go off, did you have a half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well I could go off any time at all, I - I was - as long as I arra
nged - things I could go off any time. Oh I went - I had good holidays, I went abroad, nearly every year, yes. Yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Sounds very generous?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes. Oh yes, I was very lucky. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would you go into the town, Oban, for the evening or was there nothing really to go there for?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh there was picture houses, yes, yes, go to the pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would that be before the war, before the first world war would there be a picture house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 The first war I was in - in Teerault, just a small v
illage outside Oban. But - the second world war - oh yes, there was pictures, during the first world war I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 There was nothing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 When would be the first time that you went to something like that, would that be before the first war or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh it was during the - during - it would be during the first world war, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 What about theatre, music hall, that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 We didn't - nothing like that then, no. No, not in Fort William at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would they have concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh yes, concerts, yes, oh yes, very popular, yes, yes, oh yes. Enjoyed the concerts - very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Can you tell me how the town struck you when you first arrived, what sort of things seemed to you different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well I didn't - it didn't strike me - you know, I knew - well I'd seen pictures and you could read books and - you knew what to expect.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 So you weren't at all surprised?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No I wasn't. The only thing that surprised me was that drunk woman. I never got over that. No. 'Cos I was s
urprised to see the big buildings but - I knew that that's what they had there, you know I wasn't expecting to see - little cottages here and there, I knew it wouldn't be like that. I - I wasn't - I wasn't surprised - at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Was it a rather sort of lonely life or were you able to make friends locally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
I can - oh yes, I didn't - I never felt lonely. I could all - I did a lot of knitting, and - I had such a lot of mending to do and - never had time to feel lonely. I never felt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15877612\charrsid16712901  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 lonely. There wa
s always plenty of mending to be done in those days. Not so today with their nylon stockings and their - socks and all that, they don't need to be mended at all, you don't have to mend them. I used to knit all their socks. Yes, I did, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Would they use a laundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
I did everything. Yes. Managed to do all the - washing. And ironing I did myself because they were very fussy. They - sometimes - if I was away and a woman came in - to do the cooking and perhaps she would do their laundry and their s
ocks would be ruined. They would be - they'd shrink you know. Didn't know how to wash them, there's a special way in - well you've got to be careful with woollens how you wash them. Used to spoil their woollens. Mm hm. Not properly washed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Going back a little bit earlier I wonder whether you remember your father's funeral? What happened when he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Oh I - I - I've just go a hazy recollection of father's funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You didn't remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No. It was a big big funeral. Mm. He died in Glasgow and the remains were - taken home. Buried in Borve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did a lot of people go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Oh yes, everybody on the island went. Yes. And they had to carry the remains all the way you know, take it in turns. There was no cars in those days. Or lorries or anything, today is so different. Nobody walks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did you wear mourning clothes for a long time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Well, I suppose they would - no, I suppose they would wear - not for a long time, no. No, they don't believe in mourning - much here you know. They never 
wear - I don't think people wear mourning nowadays do they. No. Yes, mm hm. Mm hm. Perhaps wear a band on your arm. That was about all I think you wore, the men wore a band on their arm. And I'm not sure - I can't remember if the women wore a bands on the
ir arms, I can't remember that. The men used to wear a band on their arm. Some did. On their Sunday suit you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 You've told me about your own jobs and Callum told us about his and we know about your sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 I was wondering about the other members of the family, what sort of jobs they had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 
Well Lisa was always at home. You see, my mother was here, and my sister was here, she was in school. And Teresa never went out to work, she was at home with my mother. They - they'd the croft
 and the cow and the - all the rest of it. She did the planting of potatoes and all that sort of thing you know. They worked very hard. Turning the ground and everything, Teresa did all that, Mrs Campbell. I don't think you met her. The wife was over on S
aturday they were telling me. She was over on Saturday. Well she was the one that was always at home there's always a - one girl always stayed with the mother to help. She needed it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 And what about the other sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Well they were away. My eldest sister - yes, well she got married - quite young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 Did she marry here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 No, she married in Oban, she was staying in Oban.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9402713 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 She married a man on the mainland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11023910 MJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 He was an Aberd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15877612\charrsid16712901 eeni}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9313509\charrsid16712901 an but he was in - he was in.
